title: Output parameter should display in data set dialog.
description: When calling a stored procedure from the Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. Currently, the output parameter is not being displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: The output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR: 1. Call a stored procedure from the Oracle database. 2. Observe that the query result is stored in an output parameter. 3. Open the edit data set dialog. 4. Verify that the output parameter is displayed in the dialog.
